```julia
function count_model_rows(df_cars::DataFrame)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> g -> length(g)
end
```

This function uses the `groupby` function from Julia's DataFrames.jl package to group the data by the `:model` column and then applies a function that returns the number of rows in each group (which is just the length of the grouped data). The resulting output will be a vector of counts corresponding to each unique model in the dataset.
